get.description: Get authorization options for the targeted account.

400.description: A required header is missing. Correct the request and try again.

source:
curl -X GET \
  -H "accept: application/json" \
  -H "Account: <account_ID>" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer <bearer_token>" \
  --url 'https://us.icr.io/api/v1/auth'

getAuthOptions := containerRegistryService.NewGetAuthOptions()

authOptions, response, err := containerRegistryService.GetAuth(getAuthOptions)
if err != nil {
  panic(err)
}
b, _ := json.MarshalIndent(authOptions, "", "  ")
fmt.Println(string(b))

auth_options = container_registry_service.get_auth().get_result()

print(json.dumps(auth_options, indent=2))

patch.description: Update authorization options for the targeted account.

requestBody.description: A JSON document containing the requested updates.

400.description: A required header is missing or invalid. Correct the request and try again.

403.description: You do not have access to perform the requested operation. You must have either Manager or Billing Manager roles on the targeted account to perform this action.

source:
curl -X PATCH \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -H "Account: <account_ID>" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer <bearer_token>" \
  -d "{\"iam_authz\":true}" \
  --url 'https://us.icr.io/api/v1/auth'

updateAuthOptions := containerRegistryService.NewUpdateAuthOptions()
updateAuthOptions.SetIamAuthz(true)

response, err := containerRegistryService.UpdateAuth(updateAuthOptions)
if err != nil {
  panic(err)

response = container_registry_service.update_auth(
  iam_authz=True
).get_result()

print(json.dumps(response, indent=2))

post.description: Similar to the API for `docker build`. Builds an image in the cloud and pushes to one of your namespaces in the registry.

parameters.description: The IBM Cloud IAM refresh token that you receive when you log in to IBM Cloud. Your refresh token is stored in your IBM Cloud config file: `~/.bluemix/config.json`
parameters.name: RefreshToken

parameters.description: The full name for the image that you want to build, including the registry URL and namespace.
parameters.name: t

parameters.description: Specify the location of the Dockerfile relative to the build context. If not specified, the default is 'PATH/Dockerfile', where PATH is the root of the build context.
parameters.name: f

parameters.description: If set to true, cached image layers from previous builds are not used in this build. Use this option if you expect the result of commands that run in the build to change.
parameters.name: nocache

parameters.description: If set to true, the base image is pulled even if an image with a matching tag already exists on the build host. The base image is specified by using the FROM keyword in your Dockerfile. Use this option to update the version of the base image on the build host.
parameters.name: pull

parameters.description: If set to true, the filesystem of the built image is reduced to one layer before it is pushed to the registry. Use this option if the number of layers in your image is close to the maximum for your storage driver.
parameters.name: squash

parameters.description: A JSON key-value structure that contains build arguments. The value of the build arguments are available as environment variables when you specify an `ARG` line which matches the key in your Dockerfile.
parameters.name: buildargs

parameters.description: If set to true, build output is suppressed unless an error occurs.
parameters.name: quiet

200.description: A stream of JSON objects that contain the output from the build host.

get.description: List all images in namespaces in a targeted IBM Cloud account.

parameters.description: Lists images that are stored in the specified namespace only. Query multiple namespaces by specifying this option for each namespace. If this option is not specified, images from all namespaces in the specified IBM Cloud account are listed.
parameters.name: namespace

parameters.description: Includes IBM-provided public images in the list of images. If this option is not specified, private images are listed only. If this option is specified more than once, the last parsed setting is the setting that is used.
parameters.name: includeIBM

parameters.description: Includes private images in the list of images. If this option is not specified, private images are listed. If this option is specified more than once, the last parsed setting is the setting that is used.
parameters.name: includePrivate

parameters.description: Includes tags that reference multi-architecture manifest lists in the image list. If this option is not specified, tagged manifest lists are not shown in the list. If this option is specified more than once, the last parsed setting is the setting that is used.
parameters.name: includeManifestLists

parameters.description: Displays Vulnerability Advisor status for the listed images. If this option is specified more than once, the last parsed setting is the setting that is used.
parameters.name: vulnerabilities

parameters.description: Lists images that are stored in the specified repository, under your namespaces. Query multiple repositories by specifying this option for each repository. If this option is not specified, images from all repos are listed.
parameters.name: repository

400.description: A required header is missing. Correct the request and try again.

401.description: You are not authorized to view the requested resource, or your IBM Cloud bearer token is invalid. Correct the request and try again.

403.description: You do not have access to the specified namespace. Choose another namespace.

404.description: No namespaces were found for the targeted account. Add a namespace or target a different account. Alternatively, specify the option to include IBM-provided public images.

post.description: Create a new tag in a private registry that refers to an existing image in the same region. If the fromimage has Red Hat signatures and the toimage is in a different repository, those signatures are copied to that repository.

parameters.description: The name of the image that you want to create a new tag for, in the format <REPOSITORY>:<TAG>. Run `ibmcloud cr images` or call the `GET /images/json` endpoint to review images that are in the registry.

parameters.description: The new tag for the image, in the format <REPOSITORY>:<TAG>.
parameters.name: toimage

AccountParam.description: The unique ID for your IBM Cloud account.
AccountParam.name: Account

ServerUnavailable.description: Unable to authenticate with IBM Cloud. Try again later.

IAM.description: The IBM Cloud IAM access token that you receive when you log in to IBM Cloud. Run `ibmcloud iam oauth-tokens` to retrieve your access token.

AuthOptions.description: The authorization options for the targeted IBM Cloud account

iam_authz.description: Enable role based authorization when authenticating with IBM Cloud IAM

private_only.description: Restrict account to only be able to push and pull images over private connections

AccountSettings.description: Account settings for the targeted IBM Cloud account

platform_metrics.description: Opt in to IBM Cloud Container Registry publishing platform metrics

Config.description: The configuration data about a container.

ArgsEscaped.description: True if command is already escaped (Windows specific)

AttachStderr.description: If true, standard error is attached

AttachStdin.description: If true, standard input is attached, which makes possible user interaction

AttachStdout.description: If true, standard output is attached

Cmd.description: Command that is run when starting the container

Entrypoint.description: Entrypoint to run when starting the container

Env.description: List of environment variables to set in the container

ExposedPorts.description: A list of exposed ports in a format [123:{},456:{}]

Hostname.description: The host name of the container

Image.description: Name of the image as it was passed by the operator (eg. could be symbolic)

Labels.description: List of labels set to this container

MacAddress.description: The MAC Address of the container

NetworkDisabled.description: If true, containers are not given network access

OnBuild.description: ONBUILD metadata that were defined on the image Dockerfile https://docs.docker.com/engine/reference/builder/#onbuild

Shell.description: Shell for shell-form of RUN, CMD, ENTRYPOINT

StdinOnce.description: If true, close stdin after the 1 attached client disconnects

StopTimeout.description: Timeout (in seconds) to stop a container

Tty.description: Attach standard streams to a tty, including stdin if it is not closed

User.description: The user that will run the command(s) inside the container

Volumes.description: List of volumes (mounts) used for the container

WorkingDir.description: Current working directory (PWD) in the command will be launched

Duration.description: A Duration represents the elapsed time between two instants as an int64 nanosecond count.

HealthConfig.title: Configuration settings for the HEALTHCHECK feature.

Retries.description:
The number of consecutive failures needed to consider a container as unhealthy.
Zero means inherit.

Test.description:
The test to perform to check that the container is healthy.
An empty slice means to inherit the default.
The options are:
{} : inherit healthcheck
{"NONE"} : disable healthcheck
{"CMD", args...} : exec arguments directly
{"CMD-SHELL", command} : run command with system's default shell

ImageBulkDeleteError.description: Information about a failure to delete an image as part of a bulk delete.

message.description: The English text message associated with the error code.

ImageBulkDeleteResult.description: The results of a bulk image delete request.
ImageBulkDeleteResult.title: Details returned from a bulk image deletion.

error.description: A map of digests to the error object that explains the failure.

success.description: A list of digests which were deleted successfully.

ListImageDigestOptions.description: The input to the ImageDigestLists request

exclude_va.description: ExcludeVA returns the digest list with no VA scan results

include_ibm.description: When true, API will return the IBM public images if they exist in the targeted region.

repositories.description: Repositories in which to restrict the output. If left empty all images for the account will be returned.

ImageInspection.description: An image JSON output consistent with the Docker Remote API

Architecture.description: The processor architecture used to build this image, and required to run it

Comment.description: A plain text description of the image

Container.description: The ID of the container which created this image

Created.description: The unix timestamp for the date when the image was created

DockerVersion.description: The Docker version used to build this image

ManifestType.description: Media type of the manifest for the image

Os.description: The operating system family used to build this image, and required to run it

OsVersion.description: The version of the operating system used to build this image

Parent.description: The ID of the base image for this image

Size.description: The size of the image in bytes

VirtualSize.description: The sum of the size of each layer in the image in bytes

ImageManifest.description: A container image manifest in JSON format. Check the Content-Type response header for the manifest type.

created.description: The build date of the image

manifestType.description: The type of the image, such as 'Docker Image Manifest V2, Schema 2' or 'OCI Image Manifest v1'

size.description: The size of the image in bytes

ImageDigestRepos.description: A map of image repositories to tags

ImageDigestTags.description: A map of tags to Vulnerability Advisor reports

account.description: The IBM Cloud account that owns the namespace

crn.description: If the namespace has been assigned to a resource group, this is the IBM Cloud CRN representing the namespace

resource_created_date.description: When the namespace was assigned to a resource group

resource_group.description: The resource group that the namespace is assigned to

updated_date.description: When the namespace was last updated

NamespaceDetailsList.description: Details of authorized namespaces in the targeted IBM Cloud account

Plan.description: The plan for the targeted IBM Cloud account

Quota.description: Current usage and limits for the targeted IBM Cloud account.

QuotaDetails.title: Information about the requested quotas for the targeted IBM Cloud account in the targeted registry.

storage_bytes.description: Storage quota or usage in bytes. The value -1 denotes "Unlimited".

traffic_bytes.description: Traffic quota or usage in bytes. The value -1 denotes "Unlimited".

store.description: Storage quota in bytes. The value of Max Uint64 (18446744073709551615) denotes "Unlimited".

traffic.description: Traffic quota or usage in bytes. The value of Max Uint64 (18446744073709551615) denotes "Unlimited".

QuotaUpdate.title: Modifications to the requested quotas for the targeted IBM Cloud account in the targeted registry.

storage_megabytes.description: Storage quota in megabytes. The value -1 denotes "Unlimited".

traffic_megabytes.description: Traffic quota in megabytes. The value -1 denotes "Unlimited".

store.description:
Requested storage quota in megabytes. The value of Max Uint64 (18446744073709551615) denotes "Unlimited".
This value is ignored if storage_megabytes is set to a non-zero value.

traffic.description:
Requested traffic quota in megabytes. The value of Max Uint64 (18446744073709551615) denotes "Unlimited".
This value is ignored if traffic_megabytes is set to a non-zero value.

RemoteAPIImage.description: Information about an image, in a format consistent with the Docker Remote API format.

RequestError.title: A typed error returned to users.

RestoreResult.description: The result of restoring tags for a digest. In a successful request the digest is always restored, and zero or more of its tags may be restored.

successful.description: Successful is a list of tags that were restored

unsuccessful.description: Unsuccessful is a list of tags that were not restored because of a conflict

RetentionPolicy.description: A document that contains the image retention settings for a namespace

images_per_repo.description: Determines how many images will be retained for each repository when the retention policy is executed. The value -1 denotes 'Unlimited' (all images are retained)

namespace.description: The namespace to which the retention policy is attached.

retain_untagged.description: Determines if untagged images are retained when executing the retention policy. This is false by default meaning untagged images will be deleted when the policy is executed.

RetentionPolicyList.description: A map of namespace names to retention policies

RootFS.description: RootFS contains information about the root filesystem of a container image

BaseLayer.description: Descriptor for the base layer in the image

Layers.description: Descriptors for each layer in the image

Tags.description: A list of tags for an image.

Trash.description: Details of the tags and days until expiry

TrashList.description: A map of digests in trash, to tags and days until expiry

VAReport.description: The VA Report for a given image

configurationIssueCount.description: Number of configuration issues in the image

exemptIssueCount.description: Total number of issues in the image that were exempted by an exemption policy

issueCount.description: Total number of issues in the image

vulnerabilityCount.description: Number of vulnerabilities in the image

buildoutput.description: The output from the build host

namespaces.description: A list of authorized namespaces in the targeted IBM Cloud account

progressdetail.description: Progress detail output from the build API.
